📹 Video Conferencing App
A full-featured video conferencing web application built 
using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, WebRTC, and Socket.IO. 

It includes features like real-time video/audio calls, screen sharing, 
whiteboard drawing, file sharing, and session recording.

🚀 Features
✅ Real-time video and audio communication (WebRTC)

🧑‍🤝‍🧑 Multiple users can join a room

🖥️ Screen sharing

📝 Collaborative whiteboard

📁 File sharing between participants

🎥 Record and download your session

🔗 Shareable meeting links


📦 Technologies Used
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Backend: Node.js, Express.js

WebRTC for peer-to-peer media communication

Socket.IO for real-time signaling and drawing

📁 Project Structure

codealpha-video-conferencing/
├── client/
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── style.css
│   └── script.js
├── server/
│   └── server.js
├── package.json
├── README.md
⚙️ Installation
Clone the repository


npm install
Start the server


node server/server.js
Ensure port 3001 is not already in use. If needed, change it in server.js.

🌐 Usage
Open your browser and go to:


http://localhost:3001
Click "Join Meeting" to enter the default room or create a custom room using a URL like:


http://localhost:3001/?room=myCustomRoom
Use features like:

"Generate Link" → Create a room share link

"Share Screen" → Share your screen

"Whiteboard" → Draw collaboratively

"File Share" → Send files to others

"Record" → Start/Stop recording your own stream


🛑 Troubleshooting
Port already in use:
Error: EADDRINUSE
➤ Kill the process using the port or change the port number in server.js.

Video not showing up:
➤ Ensure you’ve granted camera/microphone permissions in the browser.

